               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i0">
                     <locus from="1r" to="13v">1r-13v</locus>
                     <textLang xml:lang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title type="acephalous apodous" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT0049IHA#s25IHA">قران, Eighteenth ǧuz’ (18/30)</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#1r">-1r</locus>ِفَقُلِ الحَمْدُ لِله</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#12v">-12v</locus>لَّا يَخْلُقُوْنَ شَيْأً وَّهُم يُخْلَقُوْنَ وَلَا يَمْلِكُوْنَ \ لأ <note>The last word is the catchword</note>
                     </explicit>
                     <note>23:28-25:3.Text begins in the middle verse 23:28 and ends in the middle of verse 25:3. Diacritic of ḏāl-s placed at the level of the upper part of the stroke, on its external side; diacritic of final nūn-s placed closed to the bottom of the curve. Numerous words completed on the following line. Religious formula "lā ilah illā huwa" enhanced (5r, talwīn). Red circles as verse markers. Catchwords, maybe written by the same hand as the matn. Quires sewn together, higher than the binding.</note>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
